  "created": "2025-10-15",
  "description": "The Cell Wall Integrity (CWI) pathway responds to cell wall stress via surface sensors (Wsc1/2/3, Mid2, Mtl1) detecting cell wall damage or osmotic stress. Sensors activate Rho1 GTPase via GEFs (Rom1/2). Rho1-GTP activates Pkc1 kinase, initiating a MAPK cascade: Bck1 (MAPKKK) \u2192 Mkk1/2 (MAPKK) \u2192 Slt2/Mpk1 (MAPK). Activated Slt2 phosphorylates transcription factors Rlm1 and SBF (Swi4/Swi6), inducing cell wall biosynthesis genes. Rho1 also directly activates \u03b2-1,3-glucan synthase for immediate wall repair.",
  "id": "yeast_cell_wall_integrity",
  "keywords": [
    "cell wall integrity",
    "Pkc1",
    "Rho1",
    "Slt2",
    "Rlm1",
    "MAPK cascade"
  ],
  "lastUpdated": "2025-10-15",
